node.text: @_.syawal._ you can celebrate with your loved ones, people in your household. Don’t pretend that you won’t be using your phone 90% of the time when you’re visiting. There’s hari Raya next year, the year after, and so on. So please jangan nak drama lebih. Thanks.

For the first time, Muslims in Singapore cannot break their fasts together with friends and extended family, or congregate to have their prayers at the mosques. 
How are they celebrating Ramadan with the Circuit Breaker in place? We speak to some of them to find out.
